# Debugging a Node.js Memory Leak: Systematic Approach

## Phase 1: Confirm and Reproduce

### 1.1 Verify It's Actually a Memory Leak
```bash
# Monitor memory usage over time
$ watch -n 1 'ps -eo pid,comm,rss | grep node'

# Or use built-in Node.js monitoring
$ node --inspect your-app.js
# Then open chrome://inspect and check Memory tab
```

**Key indicators:**
- RSS (Resident Set Size) grows continuously
- Heap usage doesn't return to baseline after GC
- Application slows down over time
- Process crashes with "JavaScript heap out of memory"

### 1.2 Create Reproduction Scenario
```javascript
// Test script to isolate the leak
const testLeak = async () => {
  const leakyData = [];

  // Simulate suspected leak pattern
  setInterval(() => {
    const data = new Array(10000).fill('*');
    leakyData.push(data);
    console.log(`Array count: ${leakyData.length}, Memory: ${process.memoryUsage().heapUsed / 1024 / 1024} MB`);
  }, 100);
};

testLeak();
```

